<item>
            <title>[DATACMNS-408] Guard against invalid values when resolving pagination and sorting parameters from web requests</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/DATACMNS-408</link>
                <project id="10510" key="DATACMNS">Spring Data Commons</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;example of invalid value&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;page=-1 (negative numeric)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;size=a (not numeric)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;sort= (not specified)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;sort=,DESC (not specified property of sort target)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;etc ...&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Current implementation of the PageableHandlerMethodArgumentResolver is occurred IllegalArgumentException, and http response status is returned 500(Internal Server Error) on the default settings of SpringMVC.&lt;br/&gt;
I think a best that http response status is returned 400(Bad Request).&lt;/p&gt;</description>
